docs/q-manager.md:52:The manager normally runs `continue`, which validates the active child session JSONL, reprompts the same child when retry remains, persists the canonical graph decision for valid results, starts the graph-selected next child when safe, and cleans the old pane only after the next child exists. Slight positive wording mistakes are normalized only when deterministic from node/status/workspace context, such as `review-outline` + `status: complete` + `outcome: complete` becoming `ready-for-plan`; ambiguous, negative, human, blocked, or follow-up outcomes still reprompt or stop. `start-next` / `continue` may accept explicit manager usage flags (`--manager-usage-percent` or `--manager-usage-tokens` + `--manager-usage-window`); when usage is above 80%, q-manager writes an operational handoff, marks delivery `compacting`, and queues child wakes until `manager-ready` flushes them.
